        "id": "f7af31e90e758346",
        "text": "# Formats\n"
      },
      "date": 1519640871638
    },
    {
      "type": "add",
      "item": {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "id": "21333427-dc74-4059-8f20-b991ef80e5cd",
        "text": "A key decision is the formatting of the text such that minimal [[markup language]] can be inserted to assist the software agent while maintaining readability. To be a Ricardian Contract, it has to be parsable both by the program and by a human reader. Further, the format has to support a [[canonical form]] hash ([[cryptographic hash function]]), that is, have a way of delivering a hash over contents that does not change due to common [[serialisation]] and transmission artifacts."
      },
