      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "17d4a9075a16e3a7",
      "text": "Although private key signatures are well studied and are subject of legal frameworks such as the European digital signature directive, Grigg suggests that the trail of hashes - entanglement - forms a more effective evidence of intent  than a private key signature."
